    @{fg highlight}* SVObjects marked with an Asterisk will only work, when               @{fg text}
    @{fg highlight}  the mentioned external programs (usually freely distributable        @{fg text}
    @{fg highlight}  software from AmiNet) also have been installed and set up as needed. @{fg text}
      (If not set up, these may be disabled via controlpad STATUS=DISABLED.)

   There's also an @{"Unpack.svobject" LINK /PackerSupport/Unpack.doc/Main 0 } in the PackerSupport-Directory,
   which allows reading of packed files without explicitely unpacking
   these before (supports XPK and PP20). It also supports reading of Mac-written
   .HQX files (BinHex compression) without having to extract the data fork before.

   It is as well possible to save graphics as @{"C or Asm-Sourcecode" LINK SVOBJECT_CSource }.

   @{fg highlight}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}
     @{i}GIF is obsolete - you neither should use nor support it any longer. If
     you are doing WWW design, use PNG and JPEG instead. It's important !@{ui}

     If you need to handle GIF graphics (e.g for conversion to PNG), just
     install one of the available GIF datatypes - and reading will work.
   @{fg highlight}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{fg text}


