                   as well as Picasso96. All these drivers now are mutually
                   exclusive - the only possible parallel use now is together
                   with the CyberGraphX driver (since they fixed this nasty
                   bug as with V1.27 or 1.28 AFAIK)
                 - if you want to try parallel use nevertheless, just copy
                   the files back from LIBS:svstorage/ to LIBS:svdrivers/
                 - there's also the possibility to install these to
                   LIBS:svdrivers/  and add their names to the file
                   ENV:superview-library/svdrivers.exclude  (respectively ENVARC:),
                   so that you can try to add them on demand (use "+" fromout
                   SVPrefs)

